❗️The first working meeting of the National Health Committee and the Public Health Subcommittee of the Medical Committee of the European Parliament took place, where a number of important issues of cooperation between Ukraine and EU member states in the field of health care were discussed. legislation to EU law;
- support of Ukrainian medicine in conditions of war;
- interactions in the pharmaceutical industry;
- development of common digital space;
- joint implementation of projects in the field of mental health care;
- cooperation in the treatment of polytrauma, rehabilitation of the wounded, provision of innovative drugs to cancer and orphan patients.

The Chairman of the Committee, Mykhailo Radutsky, expressed his gratitude to the European Union and its member states for adopting a political decision to open negotiations on Ukraine's accession to the EU. He emphasized that European integration remains a priority for our country and noted that Ukraine has already fulfilled 78% of its obligations in the field of health care. I am within the framework of the association agreement with the EU. 📲Details

